# Ernest local scheduled jobs.
# Install with: crontab ~/.ernest-cc/crontab.example
# The installer copies this into ~/.ernest-cc/crontab.example.
#
# These run the deterministic engine directly: no model, no connectors, no auth.
# That means scheduled watch/brief/learn keep working even with no VPS and no
# Claude session open. Output lands in the vault and logs.

SHELL=/bin/zsh
ERNEST_HOME=$HOME/.ernest-cc

# Daily safe auto-update CHECK, 07:30 (before the brief). Fetches from GitHub,
# validates the new commit (health gauntlet + gate self-test) in a throwaway
# worktree, and stages a one-tap card. It does NOT auto-install — reply
# "apply update" or run `ernest update` to promote; auto-rollback on failure.
# A canary/soak surface (e.g. a VPS) can use `update auto` to apply automatically.
30 7 * * * "$ERNEST_HOME/bin/ernest" update check >> "$ERNEST_HOME/logs/cron.log" 2>&1

# Morning brief, weekdays 08:00
0 8 * * 1-5 "$ERNEST_HOME/bin/ernest" brief >> "$ERNEST_HOME/logs/cron.log" 2>&1

# Ambient watch, weekdays 11:00 and 16:00
0 11,16 * * 1-5 "$ERNEST_HOME/bin/ernest" watch >> "$ERNEST_HOME/logs/cron.log" 2>&1

# Weekly self-improvement summary, Fridays 17:00
0 17 * * 5 "$ERNEST_HOME/bin/ernest" learn >> "$ERNEST_HOME/logs/cron.log" 2>&1

# Optional model-enriched variant (requires Claude CLI + sign-in):
# 0 8 * * 1-5 cd "$ERNEST_HOME" && claude -p "/ernest-brief" >> logs/cron.log 2>&1
